Seven years ago, Taraba state Internal Generated Revenue IGR which basically control by the state civil servants under the state board of international revenue was was far less than N300 million. Leakages, laxity, corruption, lark of train Manpower and in inadequate supervision was identified as factors mitigating the state highest body of income. Shortly after clinching to power, in 2015, Governor Darius Ishaku of the state approached the state house of assembly for restructuring of the board of internal revenue. An approach which change the former name of the board  from Taraba State Board of Internal Revenue to Taraba State Revenue Service, the house of assembly also restructured the constitution of the board by empowering the executive to employ digital/electronic services to monitor the inflow of taxes and other financial income of the state. The governor further engage most of the civil servants under Taraba State Revenue Service TSRS into training both within and outside the country through workshops for effective operations. LEADERSHIP gathered through record available that the governor’s efforts to revamp the revenue sector yielded positive result under his first year in office. The state IGR which was less than N300 million naira between 2014 to 2015 rose to N4. 155, 053, 815: 83. the move that impress the government to engage external consultants to add up input for generation of the state revenue. In 2016, records available shows that the state IGR rose to N4, 455, 991, 318: 34.. Subsequent data shows that the governor in his relentless quest to improve the state IGR deployed several means to pave ways that would boost the revenue generation which includes discipline of erring staff, motivation of staff through awards, blockage of linkages, massive awareness on tax payments and creation of single revenue treasury account. The chairman, Taraba State Revenue Service Dr. Siman Ambiya’a in an interview with LEADERSHIP said Internal Generated Revenue IGR in Taraba state which use to be a mirage has been on increase within the last seven years of Governor Darius Ishaku’s administration. Ambiya’a said the IGR has been on fast increase following new initiatives adopted by the management of the state board of internal revenue.  . He further revealed that the state IGR in  2017, rose to 5. 764, 251, 233: 85.. Ambiya’a attributes the rise  of the state IGR to blockage of revenue leakages and new innovation introduced by the management within the last few years “You are aware that a lot of our services are driven by technology, that is automation, all of the road motor vehicles administration is completely automated, to a large extent all of the IGR management is also automated, that is why we call ourselves Taraba State Electronic IGR Solution. “As the years go by we try to perfect the processes by minimizing leakages and diversions, these are the areas we did not capture in previous years, which this time we try our best to bring in more tax payers into our IGR. You can see records available shows that in 2018, we made appreciable increases as our IGR hit 5, 968, 809, 483: 11. In 2019, we recorded an increase of 6.533, 106, 674: 27. in 2020, we got 8.114, 973,143:14. and last year 2021 we were able to arrive where we are today which 9. 625, 942, 713: 78. The board chairman call on the people operating businesses in the state to follow due process by paying tax to the appropriate authorities while he further urge the IGR management in the state to adhere strictly on the lay down rules of their engagements as proscribe by the state laws. 